    "what_description": "Verbascum cylleneum is a perennial plant endemic to Greece, belonging to the family Scrophulariaceae. It has a stout stem, reaching up to 60 cm in height, with leaves that are lanceolate to elliptical in shape, and 8-15 cm in length. The leaves are covered with a dense, white tomentum, and the inflorescence is a terminal spike, consisting of numerous flowers that are yellow to purple in color. Each flower is 3-4 cm in diameter, with five petals, and is surrounded by a pair of bracts that are longer than the calyx. The plant produces small, capsule-like fruits that contain numerous seeds, and it typically blooms from June to August.",
