    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Verbascum cylleneum are attributed to its antioxidant activity, which helps protect against oxidative stress and cell damage. Its anti-inflammatory properties contribute to the reduction of swelling and pain, making it a potential treatment for various inflammatory diseases. The plant's antimicrobial properties have been shown to inhibit the growth of microorganisms, including bacteria and fungi, making it effective against infections. Additionally, Verbascum cylleneum's antispasmodic properties help alleviate muscle spasms and cramps, providing relief from symptoms of conditions such as asthma and irritable bowel syndrome. Furthermore, the plant's analgesic properties make it a potential treatment for pain management, with flavonoids, such as verbascoside, and volatile oils, such as borneol, being key bioactive compounds responsible for these medicinal properties.",
