    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Verbascum cylleneum are verbascoside, iridoid glycosides, flavonoids, quercetin, and kaempferol, which contribute to its medicinal properties. Verbascoside exhibits anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and antimicrobial activities, while iridoid glycosides possess anti-inflammatory and spasmolytic properties, providing relief from muscle spasms. Flavonoids, specifically quercetin and kaempferol, have potent antioxidant effects, scavenging free radicals and protecting against oxidative stress, which can lead to various diseases. Quercetin also demonstrates anti-inflammatory and immunomodulatory activities, whereas kaempferol has been shown to have anti-cancer and anti-viral properties. The combination of these constituents in Verbascum cylleneum may provide a synergistic effect, enhancing its therapeutic potential in treating various conditions.",
